    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Economists have varying views, but the consensus is that the negative impact of immigration on wages is usually small and concentrated among specific, low-skilled groups. Many studies show that the overall effect on the average wage across a country is negligible or even slightly positive due to increased demand. The \"wage suppression\" argument is often overstated as a political talking point, while the actual impact is far more nuanced.",
